cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CR

The paper discusses scientometric evaluation and citation impact indicators, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with the organization, retrieval, and dissemination of digital information, including bibliographic data. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also relevant as it deals with the retrieval of information from large collections, including citation analysis. cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as it deals with the social and ethical implications of computing, including the evaluation of research impact. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as it deals with the analysis of social networks, including citation networks. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still relevant as it deals with the evaluation of security protocols and the impact of research in this field.
